spanishExample: ¡Hey! ¿Cuántas cosas debía tener?
englishTranslation: Hey! How many things did I have(Deber imperfect) to have?
vocabIncluded: cuánto: adverb meaning "how much?" in a question or implied question
debía: had to/must have, I had to/must have (Deber, imperfect, 1st person)

spanishExample: ¿Cuántos dólares debe tener para ir a ese lugar?
englishTranslation: How many dollars must he have in order to go to that place?
vocabIncluded: debe: must, he/she/it must (Deber, present, 3rd person)
para: "in order", "in order to" before an infinitive

spanishExample: Ah, no debo estar en el medio del camino.
englishTranslation: Ah, I must not be in the middle of the way.
vocabIncluded: debo: must, I must (Deber, present, 1st person)
del: "of the" before a masculine noun

spanishExample: Cuanto más van a ese lugar, más deben hablar.
englishTranslation: The more they go to that place, the more they must talk.
vocabIncluded: deben: must, they must (Deber, present, 3rd person plural)
hablar: to speak / to talk (Hablar infinitive)

spanishExample: Cuanto menos hacen ahora, más debo hacer después.
englishTranslation: The less they do now, the more I must do later.
vocabIncluded: debo: must, I must (Deber, present, 1st person)

spanishExample: Debemos estar en ese lugar a tiempo y tú debes estar ahí también.
englishTranslation: We must be in that place on time and you must be there too.
vocabIncluded: ahí: adverb meaning "there", especially when close to the speaker or listener
debemos:must, we must (Deber, present, 1st person plural)
debes: must, you must (Deber, present, 2nd person)

spanishExample: Debemos hacer algo en cuanto a su problema.
englishTranslation: We must do something regarding his problem.
vocabIncluded: debemos:must, we must (Deber, present, 1st person plural)

spanishExample: Deben tener cuanto quieran porque los otros no están aquí.
englishTranslation: They must have as much as they want because the others aren’t here.
vocabIncluded: cuanto used with a subjunctive to mean "as much as", as in “cuanto quiera” (pronoun)
deben: must, they must (Deber, present, 3rd person plural)
tener cuidado: "to be careful" (idiom, lit. "to have carefulness")

spanishExample: Deber estar ahí es lo único que tengo que hacer.
englishTranslation: Having(deber) to be there is the only thing I have(Tener) to do.
vocabIncluded: "lo": "the" with no noun, as in "lo bueno"
"que", meaning "that" as a conjunction (even in cases where "that" disappears in English)
ahí: adverb meaning "there", especially when close to the speaker or listener
using Tener with "que" to indicate obligation

spanishExample: Deberá decirle de la muerte de su amigo.
englishTranslation: He will have to(Deber) tell her about the death of her friend.
vocabIncluded: de used to mean "about", as in "hablar de"
deberá: will have to/must, he/she/it will have to/must (Deber, future, 3rd person)

spanishExample: Deberás hacer lo que yo te diga.
englishTranslation: You will have to(Deber) do what I tell you.
vocabIncluded: "lo que": "what" as a connector between phrases
deberás: will have to/must, you will will have to/must (Deber, future, 2nd person)
te: "you" as an indirect object ("to you", "for you")

spanishExample: Debería decirle que no pasa nada.
englishTranslation: She should tell him that it’s all good.
vocabIncluded: "que", meaning "that" as a conjunction (even in cases where "that" disappears in English)
debería: should, he/she/it should (Deber, conditional, 3rd person)

spanishExample: Debería ir a casa en vez de ir a la fiesta.
englishTranslation: I should go home instead of going to the party.

spanishExample: Debería tener un número antes de ir ahí.
englishTranslation: I should have a number before going there.
vocabIncluded: ahí: adverb meaning "there", especially when close to the speaker or listener

spanishExample: Deberías hacerlo hasta el fin.
englishTranslation: You should do it until the end.
vocabIncluded: deberías: should, you should (Deber, conditional, 2nd person)

spanishExample: Debes saber que él no ha venido nunca aquí.
englishTranslation: You must know that he hasn’t ever come here.
vocabIncluded: "que", meaning "that" as a conjunction (even in cases where "that" disappears in English)
debes: must, you must (Deber, present, 2nd person)
ha: "has", "he/she/it has" before a participle (Haber, present, 3rd person)

spanishExample: Debí decirles porque son mis amigos.
englishTranslation: I had to(Deber preterite) tell them because they are my friends.
vocabIncluded: debí: had to/must have, I  had to/must have (Deber, preterite, 1st person)

spanishExample: Debíamos decirle eso, pero no lo hicimos.
englishTranslation: We had(Deber imperfect) to tell him that, but we didn’t.
vocabIncluded: debíamos: had to/must have, we had to/must have (Deber, imperfect, 1st person plural)

spanishExample: Debías hacerlo, pero al final está bien si no lo hiciste.
englishTranslation: You had(Deber imperfect) to do it, but in the end it’s ok if you didn’t do it.
vocabIncluded: "bien": adverb meaning "well", "fine", and a variety of other positive things
debías: had to/must have, you had to/must have (Deber, imperfect, 2nd person)

spanishExample: Debieron hacer más, pero en fin, no lo hicieron.
englishTranslation: They should have(Deber preterite) done more, but anyway, they didn’t.
vocabIncluded: debieron: had to/must have, they had to/must have (Deber, preterite, 3rd person plural)
en fin: “anyway” / “in a nutshell” / “all in all” (idiom)

spanishExample: Debió hacerlo porque no había otra forma.
englishTranslation: She had(Deber preterite) to do it, because there wasn’t another way.
vocabIncluded: debió: had to/must have, he/she/it had to/must have (Deber, preterite, 3rd person)
había: "had", "he/she/it had" before a participle (Haber, imperfect, 3rd person)

spanishExample: Debiste verlo, fue bueno.
englishTranslation: You should have(Deber preterite) seen it, it was good.
vocabIncluded: debiste: had to/must have, you had to/must have (Deber, preterite, 2nd person)

spanishExample: Él debe saber que lo que hizo no está bien.
englishTranslation: He must know that what he did isn’t right.
vocabIncluded: "bien": adverb meaning "well", "fine", and a variety of other positive things
"lo que": "what" as a connector between phrases
"que", meaning "that" as a conjunction (even in cases where "that" disappears in English)
debe: must, he/she/it must (Deber, present, 3rd person)

spanishExample: Mi amigo debía ir conmigo, pero no lo hizo.
englishTranslation: My friend should have(Deber imperfect) gone with me, but he didn’t do it.
vocabIncluded: debía: had to/must have, he/she/it had to/must have (Deber, imperfect, 3rd person)

spanishExample: No deberíamos hablar con ellos, no son nuestros amigos.
englishTranslation: We shouldn’t talk to them, they aren’t our friends.
vocabIncluded: deberíamos: should, we should (Deber, conditional, 1st person plural)
hablar: to speak / to talk (Hablar infinitive)

spanishExample: No deberías decir eso.
englishTranslation: You shouldn’t say that.
vocabIncluded: deberías: should, you should (Deber, conditional, 2nd person)

spanishExample: No estoy segura de que el hombre deba ir.
englishTranslation: I’m not sure(f) that the man must go.
vocabIncluded: "que", meaning "that" as a conjunction (even in cases where "that" disappears in English)
deba: must, he/she/it must (Deber, subjunctive, 3rd person)
seguro: adjective meaning "sure" when used with Estar

spanishExample: No estoy seguro de que deba estar aquí, ¡así que adiós!
englishTranslation: I’m not sure(m) that I must be here, so goodbye!
vocabIncluded: "que", meaning "that" as a conjunction (even in cases where "that" disappears in English)
deba: must, I must (Deber, subjunctive, 1st person)
seguro: adjective meaning "sure" when used with Estar

spanishExample: No he debido hacerlo.
englishTranslation: I have not had(Deber participle) to do it.
vocabIncluded: he: "have", "I have" before a participle (Haber, present, 1st person)

spanishExample: Oh, no deberías decir esas cosas.
englishTranslation: Oh, you shouldn’t say those things.
vocabIncluded: deberías: should, you should (Deber, conditional, 2nd person)

spanishExample: Okey, pero debimos hacerlo.
englishTranslation: Okay, but we had(Deber preterite) to do it.
vocabIncluded: debimos: had to/must have, we had to/must have (Deber, preterite, 1st person plural)

spanishExample: Pues, estaré aquí hasta que debas hacerlo.
englishTranslation: Well, I’ll be here until you must do it.
vocabIncluded: estaré: "will be", "I will be" (Estar, future, 1st person)

spanishExample: Quizás debamos hablar más.
englishTranslation: Maybe we must talk more.

spanishExample: Sé que deber hacer eso es un gran problema.
englishTranslation: I know that having(Deber) to do that is a big problem.
